metadata.name: golf #15
metadata.description:
This artwork is named 'golf' due to its structure and colors. The generated abstract and random pattern may evoke a golf course - the points symbolize the golf balls and the triangular shapes, the flag of each hole. The colors used, both calming and vibrant, recall the green grass of golf courses and the surrounding natural elements.

Press "s" to save a png

metadata.name: Urban trajectories #172
metadata.description:
Title: Urban trajectories

it's a generative work that combines the precision and rigidity of a technical project with the expressiveness and creativity of informal abstract art. Made on graph paper highlighting the technical nature of the basic design. The grid creates mathematical order and clear structure, providing a stable foundation for artistic exploration.

Within some of the squares, the shapes intertwine and overlap, giving life to the geometric vision. Triangles stand out in different directions, some dotted with circles of various diameters, while rectangles of different sizes make up intriguing compositions. The colors used are black/white and a random colour, which catch the eye and create a lively contrast.

the work challenges the viewer to perceive art even in fields usually related to mathematics and engineering. The work invites reflection on the nature of order and creativity, showing how structure and artistic freedom can coexist in harmony. the work celebrates the beauty of geometric shapes and their versatility, demonstrating that even a technical foundation can be the starting point for a unique aesthetic experience.

100% code - p5.js

Press left mouse button to choose density from 1 to 15 (9000x12000) (wrong results set to 1)

Kenzo da barra

metadata.name: Sorted #239
metadata.description:
Lo-Res and Hi_Res pixels colors contract and expand, competing with each other for the sorting space.
Capture taken at 14 seconds.
Lots of possible combinations of colors and oscillation and other competitive and directional effects. 

The sixth work by HicPunks on FX Hash and our last on FXHash Beta
Made using Hydra
@HicPunks

Tags: shape, object, magnet, pixel, pixelate, animation, immovable

metadata.name: Milena’s Flowers #12
metadata.description:
Life is a path you do not walk alone.

There are 3 different flower species and some are harder to spot.
(And if you are really lucky you get to see some fireflies too)

This project is made with createjs, an old library that reproduces the Flash API.
It is an homage to my years as a Flash developer.

The preview image is 2048x2048 pixels.

- Pressing “S” you can save a 4096x4096 hires version (Only in Live mode)
- Pressing “D” you can see a debug version that gives you an insight on how the generation works

To my aunt Milena who always understood me.
Happy Birthday @---

Yours,
CCDDBB

metadata.name: Euphonic #802
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Caterpillars #88
metadata.description:
DISCLAIMER : 
I have started coding about 4 months ago and I am not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside. 

This will be kind of a charity project where the PRIMARY SALES will be 
divided as follows:
 - 60 % of primary sales will go to "Askida Fatura" -> https://askidafatura.ibb.gov.tr/
 - 20 % will go to Processing Foundation -> https://processingfoundation.org/
 - 20 % will go to Coding Train -> https://twitter.com/thecodingtrain

"Askida Fatura" is run by Istanbul Municipality and is a campaign that is used for paying the utility bills of the less fortunate living in Istanbul. On average, a couple of tezos pays one bill, and I hope to pay 5 - 10 bills with this.

I will figure out the best way to transfer the amounts later this week and the upcoming weeks, and will provide proof of transfer via my twitter. 

SINCE THIS IS CHARITY, I WILL NOT BE BURNING THE REMAINING EDITIONS!!!

Still, if you dont like what you got ping me and you can get your refund. 

twitter : https://twitter.com/evilnft
fxhash : https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/evilnft
objkt : https://objkt.com/profile/evilnft/created

about Caterpillars,

This is a humble project, does not try to achieve too much, and also wants you to not expect too much from it. 

features : 
 - 8 palettes
 - 2 different origins
 - 5 different characters
 - 6 to 49 sections
 - should be responsive, although I have only tested this on computers...

 press "s" to save a png.

metadata.name: Dashed Migration #82
metadata.description:
This is an ode to dashed lines and vector graphics.

The artwork is an animated SVG generated with Javascript.
All the animation is described and handled within the SVG.

Exports:

• plotter-ready SVG
• PNG

Controls:
• 'SPACE'/click - play/pause animation
In Live view
• 'f' - fullscreen
• 'c' - show/hide cursor
• 'e' - open the export menu
On touchscreens, the export menu can be opened with a long-press.

fx(hash) Generative Token by loackme

metadata.name: spirits, lifeforms... #44
metadata.description:
The spirits are wandering in the void, 
until reach through a new life time, where each step is tracked in a line. 
It stops when the lifeforms returns to be a spirit again.
And the cycle loops the transcendence again and again, forever...

-Rare monochromatic inverted triangles maybe can appear.


This is a work in p5.js

metadata.name: Chop Chop #153
metadata.description:
Chop Chop is a complementary collection to Caterpillars that I prepared to thank my collectors for the amazing love and interest you showed to my work. I did not want to force my way to your wallets with unsolicited thank-you nfts, so all holders of Caterpillars will have a reserve spot to mint at least 1 tokens per wallet for 0 tez ( I dont understand the reserve options fully, sorry - 128 editions reserved for holders of Caterpillars) . 

The holders of this collection will have reserve spots for my next  collection. The reserve spots will be held for one week from minting, and I prefer the unreserved editions to be fair game for anyone, so first come, first served.

I decided to re-work this older project of mine because it was going to take some time for me to prepare an independent and novel collection and also wanted to continue learning new things. The concept is Paul Klee meets Vector Math and Flow Fields, as you can see the visuals are heavily inspired by Paul Klee's work :)

Under the hood, the circles and triangles act as repulsive forces that break and distort the grid, and push the squares in their range out of their way, forming some holes in the fabric created by the same algo that made Caterpillars. 

I have only added one rarity feature which is the palette because this one uses almost all the palettes from Caterpillars (minus neon dreams). I am hoping that this project will not be about rarity, but more like a thank-you gift and an easy way to access my future work.

Well, I hope you will like it...

- Press "s" to save a png.

- Also, 33% royalty split wth the Processing Foundation, % 33 with the minters (if there will be any secondary sales) 

DISCLAIMER :
I am very very new to coding and not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside.

Thousands of color combos derived from 6 palettes including day/night variations.

Horizon color, line count, shape, angle, position.

**Planets**

**Structures**

metadata.name: System β #216
metadata.description:
α -> β is about "Increases in magnitude and decreases in computation". And still related the fleeting time in the generating process.

My role in this work is more of a discoverer than a creator. 

Try to reveal the possibilities of time perception in the generative art through negotiating with incomprehensible mathematical equations.

What I want to explore through this work is that behind the generated results, the dynamic process of generations are equally diverse and unpredictable.

When we watch the generating process displayed on the computer, changing instantly, moving, multiplying, disappearing, and we hesitate, wonder, pause, await, as if many possibilities of time perception have emerged in the fragmented moments.

_
press [1] -> β 
press [2] -> β⁰　 
press [3] -> β¹
-
Press [s] in live view to save as PNG.
Press [d] in live view to save as hi-res PNG.
-
If you need your collection in SVG format, feel free to DM me.

metadata.name: Quadrangle of My Being #129
metadata.description:
This project began as an exploration of how human beings across all sorts of cultures respond in remarkably similar ways in terms of associating sounds with shapes.  That’s a project I will have to come back to. Along the way, the outputs started to remind me of landforms seen from high above and topographical maps of imaginary terrain - the terrain of my own being.

Though the work is algorithmic through and through, I have used elements of my analog photographic work as a bits and pieces of some layers.  These photographic works are chemigrams, and are generative in their own right, arising from semi-controlled chemical reactions on dark room paper in the presence of resists and light. These chemigrams are the first topos of my being, and bringing them into this work emphasizes something I have long wanted to pursue - the rich interplay of my analog and digital practices in search of unexplored territory.

Explore some territory - you just might find the quadrangle of your being.

Collection Mechanics:
In the initial week after launch, holders of any of my past fx(hash) projects may mint free editions to the extent of their reserves on a first come, first served basis.  Beginning in the 2nd week, any unclaimed editions will be offered for public sale. 

Minting Instructions: 
1) Use the Randomized Params button to explore outputs.  
2) When a design emerges that you want to mint, lock the Seed Input param.  
3) Mint & enjoy. 

Parameter Descriptions: 
Seed Input: Each output is a unique result based on your wallet address and the seed value. If you record the seed for a given output as you explore, you can simply type in the recorded seed to retrieve it.

Project Details:
Created by Wanda Oliver (wandaoliver.tez) in July, 2023, this work is licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

The minter shares secondary royalties with the creator and a beneficiary.

Interactions:
Press [D] in live mode to download.
Press [S] in live mode to download a high resolution output suitable for framing.
Press [F] in live mode to toggle the frame on and off.
